    <mods:abstract xml:lang="en" type="theft summary">General Lopez de Santa Anna's prosthetic leg was captured during the Mexican-American War by Illinois troops (the Fourth Regiment Illinois Volunteers) after the U.S. victory in the Battle of Cerro Gordo in 1847. The prosthetic was briefly sent to the Crystal Palace in London and later shown in Washington, D.C. Despite requests to return the leg to Mexico or Texas, it is now stored under glass at the Illinois National Guard headquarters in Springfield for public viewing.
    </mods:abstract>
